Package callgraph

Class Summary
AdjacenceElement Instances of this class hold a Signature and corresponding weights.
AdjacenceList This extended HashMap is used to model the representation of the total-reduced call-graphs (documentation of total reduction, see Eichinger et al.).
ArrayListSet This data structure combines the advantages of ArrayList with a set behavior.
GraphConverter Converts graphs to different hierarchy levels (method, class or package).
GraphReader Reads in a serialized graph.
GraphWriter As the name suggests, graphs can be written here.
GraphWriterThread Serves as fallback, if the pointcuts within the instrumentation can`t catch the end of an execution.
Signature Is the representation of the signatures to work with.
SuccessorList This structure is used to hold the vertices, that succeed another vertex within AdjacenceList.
